column5: Have a great trip!  Always look forward to your reports....scenery and all....LOL

Well he made it as far as Powassan by noon today. Wayne and Leah stopped by for a quick visit at my shop. It was the first time meeting the good folks for me. We really didn't have a lot of time to chew the fat today as Wayne and Leah were anxious to get up to their great place at Temagami and I was shorthanded at my shop. Wayne will not have an excuse for not catching any fish because I know he has at least a handful of jigs to use. Good luck and enjoy yourself folks.
Have a great trip, and don't forget the pics.

...  Picked out a couple rods to get us by for 10 or so days.    Have everything here from the boat, as I cleaned it out before trading in, so more than usual to fit in the truck. Puzzle goin together in the box    and I made it all fit with room in the back seat of the cab for our food/plug in cooler and our clothes    Good thing the ford has a deeper box than a GMC !  Hope to have  a nice report in when I come back...probably just more scenery on the lake...but hell you're used to that by now!  :Gonefishing:
Enjoy your trip Wayne and we look forward to your report upon your return. Try and take a little time away from work to wet a line! Play safe   Don

The only work I have planned Don is putting the water intake line in, getting it primed and running and then rehooking my floater docks up to the crib dock. The rest of the time..play with new toy and FISH.  I know it won't go that way...but there's always hope!
hmmm...i guess "before" reports are the new fad?
Hope you have a safe and fun vacation, you deserve it!

Well Wayne have a great fishing trip enjoy the new boat remember that you are breaking in the motor so back off the throttle.Eventhough that many ponies will be dam  tempting.Take some great pics as usual give us the shots of dinner.  Imagine someone else may become the top poster of the day.Please turn the computer time into productive fishing.  What are you targeting ?fish I hope.No rivets for how many days.  I hope you don't plan on catching butterflies with the little net  Have a safe and productive vacation  MTP
have a great time enjoy the new boat

I'm sure the wife will still have a daily check list of jobs to do under the magnet on the fridge every morning.  Try to get out in the morning before she wakes up and sneak out quietly.  Have a blast Wayne.
I hate you!!!!!!!  Take me!!!!!!
Enjoy that fine vessel.....and looking forward to some purty pictures!  :-)
Enjoy it Bud. You are the envy of many. I'll get out next weekend as well. Can't wait!!!
Hey! I recognize that blue box! The last time I saw it the wind was driving it down the road at about 60mph....Thanks for snagging it for me Wayner!!! I'll pick it up in July....  Have fun!!!
The packing is worth the fun - enjoy!!
Have fun Wayne, look forward to your report.
have a good trip out there i still cant wait til the weekend comes by
Have a safe one bud!  Got my tackle packed to today  Enjoy yourself!

Thanks everyone and CH go kill a squirrel or something!  Have fun Phil....no shore lunches for ya when you get there and hopefully things don't change so that you can indeed get there. That Minnesota/Ontario fire is raging out of control. All the way up past Red Lake is also a total fire ban area. Check everything you can and Geary before heading out.

Enjoy Wayne ... and dont forget to take extra batteries for the camera ...  Next week I go to the ZEC for members opening weekend so I am only just a little jealous ... one of these days I'll have to charter you to fly us in there (blindfolded of course)
Have a great trip Wayne. Lookin' forward to you posts. Good luck on the withdrawal from rivets and OFC.
Dat's hard to say, Roger. Wivet rithdrawl.  Have the best trip Wayne. Post some pics for us shut-ins.

Thanks guys...30 late leavin but Leah's got her meds and breakfast done now so we're off in 2 minutes. Next stop Powassan and then on to Temagami. Talk to you in 10 or 11 days...when I'll make my 8000th dang post....
Wayne, give'em heck!! I hope you  nail a few nice 'eyes for the pan. Have fun!!!
Enjoy your trip Wayne.  Get in a little practice fishing for Lakair  Joey
A little late, but have a great vacation, take care of Leah, and enjoy the new toy.  Regards  John
Have a great trip. I can't wait to see your report when you come back. Lots of pics please. I'll live vicariously through you. Stay safe. 8000 posts... HOLY CRAP!!!
